title: Resident Evil 2 outbreak File#2 [Full Version]
description:
The correct title of this article is Resident Evil: Outbreak: File #2. The substitution or omission of a # sign is because of technical restrictions.
Resident Evil: Outbreak: File #2 is an online survival horror game developed and published by Capcom. It was released for the PlayStation 2 in Japan on September 9, 2004, North America on April 26, 2005, and Europe on August 26, 2005.

Following the success of Outbreak in Japan, Capcom announced the release of the sequel Resident Evil: Outbreak: File #2 in fall of 2004. The same eight characters from the first title return with similar abilities, and the game once again takes place in a zombie-inhabited Raccoon City. Five new scenarios are available, and the first four are available from the beginning. In Japan the game was packaged with a demo of Devil May Cry 3 if pre-ordered.


Resident Evil: Outbreak: File 2
xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Resident Evil Outbreak File #2 continues the drastic story of when the people of Raccoon city become infected with a secret biological weapon. 
They turn into flesh-eating zombies which swarm the streets of Raccon city. 
There are few people who survived, and you must control them and get them out of the city before you become a victim to the hordes of the flesh-eating creatures.
